title: For Sale:  14" barrel 12ga. pistol non-NFA/non-Class III
location: Ft. Myers, South West Florida, Florida
postcontent:
Barrel has been cut down to 14" and the muzzle cleaned up, it has a great shot pattern. I'm selling it for what the gun cost me + aftermarket add-ons.

Here's a snap of a letter from the ATF's legal department about why this isn't a sawed off shotgun: http://i.imgur.com/pchVmp9.jpg

Short(ish) version is: this Rem. 870 was made with a pistol grip only and has never had a shoulder stock attached. Therefore by law it is a "smoothbore handgun". Legally, all shotguns are long guns and to be a long gun it must have a full length buttstock. If it NEVER has a buttstock, it can't be a long gun/shotgun, even if it fires shotshells. No shoulder stock = automatically a pistol no matter what, period.

Since pistol barrels can be as short as you want, the only restriction the ATF has on smoothbore handguns is that their overall length mustn't fall below 26" overall. This gun is 26.5" with the aftermarket chainsaw grip I've attached.

Never ever attach a shoulder stock because then this gun magically becomes a ~real~ shotgun so then it's an illegal sawed off, forever, even if you put the chainsaw grip back on! Someone got paid with your tax dollars to come up with these rules, btw. :)

title: For Sale:  Armalite Israeli Military AR-7 22 Surivial Rifle
postcontent:
Pix #1 In the late 1960's Israel ordered an unknown quantity of Armalite AR-7 22lr cal semi auto survival rifles. They made the various modifications pictured here, provided a canvas roll bag. The set was then strapped to the ejection seat in their fighter aircraft. A few years ago less than 200 of them were imported into the U.S.

Pix #2, Among the Israeli modifications was to shorten the barrel to 13 inches. Before the importer could re-sell the guns he had to attach the 3 inch simulated muzzle break to bring it back out to a legal minimum 16".

Pix #3, Nearly all the changes made to the gun were done with pre-existing parts. Note the grip is for an FAL. Forward sling swivel is for an L1A1. I'm not sure what the canvas sling was used on but it is original to the gun.

Pix #4, Close up of the barrel just ahead of the chamber. Note the serial numbered on the barrel not done on factory Armalites. Also the importer's stamp under The Armalite address.(not shown)

Pix #5, Barrel removed & stock collapsed. Package length would have been 13" had the 3" barrel extension not been added for legality. Note the front sight, it's for a K98 Mauser!(not shown)

I have decided to liquidate everything from my 30+ year collection of military guns that I do not actually use. I was a C&R license holder but am no longer. If shipment is require it will go Priority mail insured to a license holder with signature confirmation. I WILL NOT provide any SSN information, nor will I be subjected to background checks of any kind!

title: For Sale:  14" barrel 12ga. pistol non-NFA/non-Class III
location: Ft. Myers, South West Florida, Florida
postcontent:
Rem 870 12 ga, barrel cut down to 14" and the muzzle cleaned up. I'm selling it for what the gun cost me + aftermarket add-ons. Including the original box with label/model number to prove it was made & shipped with a pistol grip only which is important.

ATF letter about why this isn't a NFA/Class III weapon: http://i.imgur.com/pchVmp9.jpg

TL;DR never had a buttstock = legally a pistol no matter what, period, even if it fires shotshells. Pistol barrels can be as short as you want. Shotguns are all legally a subset of long guns, and long guns must have full size buttstocks. NEVER attach a buttstock to this pistol and it can't be a sawed off shotgun because it's never been a shotgun.

The ATF calls this a "smoothbore handgun" and they just require it to have an overall length of 26+ inches. The gun is 26.5" right now. Don't replace the chainsaw grip I put on with a normal pistol grip, that'll make it too short. It's a Shockwave Technologies Raptor grip.

This gun's a real blast, I've even busted clays with it. Email me.
